<br>
Strength is the base attribute for warrior classes, and affects the amount of melee damage you do with both slashing and crushing type weapons. Strength also affects how much weight your character can carry. Becoming encumbered can negatively affect your character, so you'll want to be sure you have adequate strength. Trolls (Midgard) are the strongest race in the game, followed by the Firbolg (Hibernia), with Albion's strongest race being the Highlander. <br>
<br>
<br>
Constitution (Con) <br>
<br>
Constitution directly affects all characters by affecting their number of hit points. Obviously, this attribute is more important for classes that expect to take a lot of damage (tank types) but you can never have too much Constitution regardless of your class. After level 6, you will lose Constitution points upon death. If you are resurrected by another player, you regain these points. If you must release to your bind spot, be sure to visit an NPC healer for healing. Dwarves (Midgard) lead this category, while Highlanders (Albion) and the Celt &amp; Firbolg (Hibernia) races lead their respective realms. <br>
<br>
<br>
Dexterity (Dex) <br>
<br>
Lighter weapons (Daggers, Spears and Bows) are directly influenced by this attribute. Rogue skills are also linked to Dexterity, as it takes grace to hide a person in plain sight. Even mages require a bit of Dexterity to help them land their bolt spells. Additionally, it is likely that Dexterity affects the Evasion skill. Saracens (Albion) and Lurikeen (Hibernia) are tied for first place in this statistic at 80, with the Kobold race being the most nimble from the Midgard realm. <br>
<br>
<br>
Quickness (Qui) <br>
<br>
Quickness is mostly a melee class statistic, since it affects a character's combat speed. In other words, it's directly related to how fast you swing or fire your weapon, but it does not affect such things as running speed. Since casters should be doing very little melee, this is not a very important attribute for them. Lurikeen (Hibernia) are the quickest in the world of Camelot, with the Avalonian leading Albion and Kobolds leading Midgard. <br>
<br>
<br>
Intelligence (Int) <br>
<br>
Intelligence determines power (mana) levels for all Albion pure casters and Hibernia's Elemental casters. This attritbute may also affect resistances, although that has yet to be determined. Avalonians (Albion) are the most intelligent of all races, while the Elves are for Hibernia. Midgard has little use for this attribute and all races in that realm are of equal intelligence. <br>
<br>
<br>
Piety (Pie) <br>
<br>
Piety is a measure of a priest's connection with his or her god. Much like intelligence for Elemental casters, this attribute affects a priest's power (mana) levels. All Midgard casters use Piety as their determining stat for power and cleric types in Albion use it as well. Hibernia seems to have no use for this attribute, yet all races start with a base of 60 in piety. <br>
<br>
<br>
Empathy (Emp) <br>
<br>
Much like a priest's connection to their god, Empathy is a character's connection to Nature. The nature-loving Hibernians make use of this attribute for their healing powers. Firbolg are the leaders in Empathy, while all other races have a base score of 60. <br>
<br>
<br>
Charisma (Cha) <br>
<br>
Charisma is a measure of how your character is perceived in the eyes of others. It is very important to Bards, Minstrels, and Skalds, as they all rely on that statistic for their songs. All races start at a base 60 of Charisma.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=2.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br><a self href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.threadControl?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/blueMoon/deleteThread.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/ftempestnightfrm4.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub31.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpaddin